import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['precipitation'] = pd.to_numeric(data['precipitation'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['precipitation'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['precipitation'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Precipitation')
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['precipitation'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Precipitation')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.to_period('M')
    monthly_avg_temp = data.groupby('month')['temp'].mean().reset_index()
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.plot(monthly_avg_temp['month'].astype(str), monthly_avg_temp['temp'])
    
    plt.title('How does the temperature vary throughout the year in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Month')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature (°F)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Temperature'], loc='upper right')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['cloud_cover'] = pd.to_numeric(data['cloud_cover'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['cloud_cover'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['cloud_cover'], bins=10, color='skyblue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['cloud_cover'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['cloud_cover'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Cloud Cover')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cloud cover in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['daylight_hours'] = data['day_length'] / 3600

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['daylight_hours'])
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Daylight Hours')
    plt.title('How does the amount of daylight vary throughout the year in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Daylight Hours'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
